messages.message:
@jack.robbins happy to share thoughts!

This didn't come from an existing/prospective customer's perspective, but this did come from putting my shoes in the place of a reviewer.

Cleaning functions are an important and (I'm guessing) widely used feature that allow us to create more unified, consistent outputs that play nice with downstream systems & processes. Cleaning will largely rely on LLMs, and we know how that can be sometimes :lil_nervous: So it could be helpful to reviewers to presciently review the original source pre-cleaning.
